“We weren’t used to wearing such clothes,” says Degei, referring to his colorful hand-woven turban, dark blouse, and bright skirt.
"Before that, we wore only plant leaves on the body."
Papua is the poorest province in Indonesia, with 28% of the population living below the poverty line and one of Asia’s worst statistics on infant mortality and illiteracy.
It is also a rich country in Indonesia.
Just 100 km from Pania, a mountainous province of about 153,000 inhabitants in New Jersey, Grasberg is the largest and most profitable gold mine in the world, owned by Freeport McMoran, a Phoenix-based company.
