The Spanish league, clearly irritated by the departure of one of the biggest football stars, attempted to prevent Neymar from making the transition, claiming that PSG was violating the FFP by doing so.
"This is a clear case of 'monetary doping' with the club and the state," La Liga President Javier Tebas told Spanish newspaper AS, referring to the fact that PSG is primarily owned by Qatar.
Arsenal manager Arsene Wenger, whose club is owned by the American sports magnate, shares La Liga’s view that the state is funding the club.
