Among the dead are their editor and source of inspiration, Riodoce co-founder Javier Valdez Cardenas.
"The biggest mistake is living in Mexico and being a journalist," Valdez wrote in one of his many books on drug violence.
His absence makes a deep feeling, although his presence can be felt everywhere on the facade of the Riodoce building, a large picture of Valdez, pointing to the middle finger with the letter “Justice,” and two 30-year-old reporters, Aaron Ibarra and Miriam Ramirez, wear T-shirts depicting his smiling face with glasses or his characteristic Panama hat.
