Although a separate state prosecutor’s office was established in 2010 to deal with journalists’ cases, according to the Committee for the Protection of Journalists, only two cases have been prosecuted.
As with most annual homicides involving drug trafficking and organised crime, which amount to thousands, journalist killers rarely go to court.
Riodoce's editorial continues to reflect the violence in Sinaloa, although their hearts are broken and the landscape is now even more dangerous.
Without the data of the murderers and justice, the security meeting will not be of much use, according to Ibarra.
